Installing Honeysnap
--------------------
Python 2.4 or greater is required

Dependencies

irclib 0.4.6 or greater  	http://python-irclib.sourceforge.net/
pypcap 1.1 or greater  		http://www.monkey.org/~dugsong/pypcap/
dpkt		 		http://monkey.org/~dugsong/dpkt/
magic				http://www.demonseed.net/~jp/code/magic.py

      
Installation on a workstation
-----------------------------

For each of these, untar the distribution file, then cd into the directory
and run setup.py as follows:

	$ wget http://www.monkey.org/~dugsong/pypcap/pypcap-1.1.tar.gz
	$ tar -xzf pypcap-1.1.tar.gz
	$ pushd pypcap-1.1
	$ make
	$ python setup.py build && sudo python setup.py install
	$ popd
	$ rm -rf pypcap-1.1*

	$ wget http://www.monkey.org/~dugsong/dpkt/dpkt-1.6.tar.gz
	$ tar -xzf dpkt-1.6.tar.gz
	$ pushd dpkt  
	$ make
	$ python setup.py build && sudo python setup.py install
	$ popd
	$ rm -rf dpkt-1.6*

irclib and magic can also be installed with easy_install.
                               
	$ sudo easy_install python-irclib
	$ sudo easy_install magic

If you don't have easy_install, get it by doing the following:

	$ wget http://peak.telecommunity.com/dist/ez_setup.py
	$ sudo python ez_setup.py
        
                 
Installation on a honeywall
---------------------------

Note: You cannot do the above steps on the production honeywall,
as it has no gcc compiler, make, etc.  Do:

	$ sudo yum install gcc 

Then you must install python 2.4 or later.

For Fedora Core 3, create "/etc/yum.repos.d/python24.repo" with the following lines:

  [python24]
  name=Fedora Core $releasever - $basearch - Python 2.4
  baseurl=http://www.python.org/ftp/python/2.4/rpms/fedora-$releasever/
  enabled=1
  gpgcheck=1

Add the KRUD GPG key by running: 

$ sudo rpm --import http://www.python.org/ftp/python/2.4/rpms/KRUD-GPG-KEY"

Install Python 2.4 by running: 

$ sudo yum install python2.4

Then follow the instructions above, but replacing calls to 'python' with 'python2.4'. e.g.

$ sudo python2.4 setup.py install

You will also need to use python 2.4 to install easy_install

$ sudo python2.4 ez_setup.py


Running honeysnap
=================

To install honeysnap, run

	$ sudo python setup.py install

from within the honeysnap directory.

Try to execute 'honeysnap':

	$ honeysnap

You should see:

	Usage:
	honeysnap.py <config file>

	Please see the accompanying documentation for instructions on
	configuration.

If this fails, you may need to add the python bin directory to your PATH.
          
To find the prefix, use sys.prefix

$ python  
Python 2.4.3 (#1, Sep 26 2006, 19:00:44) 
[GCC 4.0.0 20041026 (Apple Computer, Inc. build 4061)] on darwin
Type "help", "copyright", "credits" or "license" for more information.
>>> import sys
>>> sys.prefix
'/opt/local/Library/Frameworks/Python.framework/Versions/2.4'

The add <prefix>/bin to your PATH.



